{{Quote|The problem in [[Llorkh]] was that he got lost and asked the wrong person for help. Parnast's smaller. There's only one street, one stable, one tav–.|The [[mage]] [[Galimer|Galimer "Longfingers"]], before being interrupted.}}

Parnast comprised a central town square, around which were built several dozen simple structures, built within a wooden palisade.{{Cite adventurers league/Uninvited Guests|8}} The wary{{Cite adventurers league/The Black Road|16}} and hardworking Parnasters earned their living as farmers,

After Zhentarim influence in Parnast waned, the area in town around the group's old chapterhouse came to be known as ''Old Parnast''. Parnasters moved some ways south outside the walled portion of town.{{Cite adventurers league/Uninvited Guests|8}}
